result.adr_address: 58-64 Paterson St, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 58-64 Paterson St, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: El Born

reviews.text: Service was great but the food was generally bad. We had a basic brunch and the dishes were all not good. Waffle and chicken, waffle is terrible, chicken was OK but was one chicken wing and a small drumstick.the batter for the chicken wasn't great and it was bland. Smoked salmon and eggs was exactly how you would expect it and was average. The big breakfast was also just OK. The hashbrown tasted like it was fried in old oil. The sausage and bacon were tasty. I was starving and ate pretty much everything the rest of the family left behind. Also, their slow cooked ox tongue needs better seasoning but the tongue itself was fine. Wouldn't return. Casual place though with great service but shame about the food.
Excellent happy hour deal and some of the nicest tapas I've tried in town. The location is definitely for the win!

The food is really good, the staff take good care of their customers.
wouldn't suggest to go as a large group, as the atmosphere is for groups of up to 4 and perfect for couples.
Located at the exciting and happening area; Food Street, Fashion Walk in Causeway Bay. They provide good hand craft beer and various wine~
Easy to follow menus good value for money food
